1
00:00:00,477 --> 00:00:04,947
(June 6, a time for remembrance)

2
00:00:05,717 --> 00:00:10,887
(We thank and honor those who made sacrifices for our country.)

3
00:00:10,987 --> 00:00:12,257
What is June known as in Korea?

4
00:00:12,917 --> 00:00:14,456
- Month of Patriots and Veterans.
- Month of Patriots and Veterans.

5
00:00:14,457 --> 00:00:18,257
Correct. So, I'm here to introduce the special guests joining us today.

6
00:00:18,497 --> 00:00:19,696
Special guests?

7
00:00:19,697 --> 00:00:20,697
Come in, transfer students.

8
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:22,926
- Who could they be?
- Hi.

9
00:00:22,927 --> 00:00:24,126
Come on in.

10
00:00:24,127 --> 00:00:25,296
- Come on in.
- They look cute.

11
00:00:25,297 --> 00:00:26,696
Come on in.

12
00:00:26,697 --> 00:00:28,266
- Come in.
- Hi.

13
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:30,566
- What an interesting combination.
- Exactly.

14
00:00:30,567 --> 00:00:31,906
- How did they end up here together?
- The one in the middle...

15
00:00:31,907 --> 00:00:34,336
looks like a dentist I know.

16
00:00:34,337 --> 00:00:35,846
- A dentist?
- A doctor transferred...

17
00:00:35,847 --> 00:00:37,506
- to our school?
- Maybe he's an ENT doctor.

18
00:00:37,507 --> 00:00:38,546
- Nonsense.
- He looks like a dentist you know?

19
00:00:38,547 --> 00:00:40,776
- They're distinguished guests.
- He looks like...

20
00:00:40,777 --> 00:00:41,916
a principal.

21
00:00:41,917 --> 00:00:43,146
- Don't make a joke like that...
- He totally looks like a principal.

22
00:00:43,147 --> 00:00:44,346
about our distinguished guest.

23
00:00:44,347 --> 00:00:45,356
- A principal...
- Hi. We're...

24
00:00:45,357 --> 00:00:48,427
from Learning About Wars Teaches You History High School.

25
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:50,986
I'm Yong Han, as in the word "excellent." I'm Im Yong Han.

26
00:00:50,987 --> 00:00:52,396
(Im Yong Han, military historian)

27
00:00:52,397 --> 00:00:55,696
I will tell you about all the technologies used in wars.

28
00:00:55,697 --> 00:00:57,227
I'm Chae Seung Byeong, a military technology expert.

29
00:00:58,437 --> 00:01:01,036
I have a special knack of discovering blue oceans.

30
00:01:01,037 --> 00:01:02,637
I'm Her Jun, the MC specializing in discovery.

31
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:04,306
(The transfer students for the Memorial Day special)

32
00:01:04,307 --> 00:01:05,476
- Welcome!
- That was great.

33
00:01:05,477 --> 00:01:07,676
- Today is Memorial Day.
- All right. Now...

34
00:01:07,677 --> 00:01:09,376
They're experts...

35
00:01:09,377 --> 00:01:11,076
- in the history of war.
- That's right.

36
00:01:11,077 --> 00:01:12,717
I heard you were surprised when you were invited.

37
00:01:13,047 --> 00:01:14,217
I was surprised, indeed.

38
00:01:14,547 --> 00:01:15,547
Why?

39
00:01:16,887 --> 00:01:18,247
I didn't think I belonged here.

40
00:01:19,487 --> 00:01:21,726
- Come on. Why?
- Why?

41
00:01:21,727 --> 00:01:24,656
Just like Yong Han, when I was asked to be here,

42
00:01:24,657 --> 00:01:27,427
I didn't understand why I was invited here.

43
00:01:27,697 --> 00:01:29,126
But there's something I've been curious about.

44
00:01:29,127 --> 00:01:31,427
- What is it?
- I agreed to be here today...

45
00:01:31,497 --> 00:01:32,667
to solve that mystery.

46
00:01:32,797 --> 00:01:33,966
That's why I accepted the invitation.

47
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:35,037
(What made Seung Byeong decide to transfer to this school?)

48
00:01:35,307 --> 00:01:38,066
I recently got a new nickname.

49
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:39,077
What is it?

50
00:01:39,137 --> 00:01:42,647
I'm often asked if I have a younger sister who's a comedienne.

51
00:01:43,007 --> 00:01:45,816
- "Aren't you Shin Young's brother?"
- He's talking about Shin Young.

52
00:01:45,817 --> 00:01:46,916
- Many people ask me that.
- That's right.

53
00:01:46,917 --> 00:01:47,917
He looks like Shin Young.

54
00:01:47,918 --> 00:01:49,017
The moment I saw him...

55
00:01:49,217 --> 00:01:50,686
- Oh, my. They look so much alike.
- Brother.

56
00:01:50,687 --> 00:01:51,687
- They have similar eyes.
- By any chance...

57
00:01:51,688 --> 00:01:52,756
Brother, why...

58
00:01:52,757 --> 00:01:55,327
- Why didn't you say it earlier?
- Can you two smile together?

59
00:01:55,587 --> 00:01:57,127
- Do we really look alike?
- They look alike.

60
00:01:57,427 --> 00:01:59,097
- They look so much alike.
- My goodness.

61
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:01,427
He shares a resemblance with my family.

62
00:02:01,727 --> 00:02:03,226
- They look alike.
- As soon as he walked in...

63
00:02:03,227 --> 00:02:05,096
- You two look alike.
- We share a resemblance.

64
00:02:05,097 --> 00:02:07,296
Shin Young's brother runs a bakery in Dumulmeori.

65
00:02:07,297 --> 00:02:08,297
That's right.

66
00:02:08,607 --> 00:02:10,366
- Her biological brother does.
- Right.

67
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:11,876
- My brother does.
- He looks like Shin Young.

68
00:02:11,877 --> 00:02:13,606
There may be a secret behind our birth.

69
00:02:13,607 --> 00:02:14,736
Absolutely.

70
00:02:14,737 --> 00:02:16,346
There are some stars who share a resemblance with me.

71
00:02:16,347 --> 00:02:18,647
They're Kim Min Jae, Seung Byeong,

72
00:02:19,247 --> 00:02:21,987
Huh Gak, and Lee Jae Po. We all look alike.

73
00:02:22,217 --> 00:02:24,586
We all share a similarity in our facial features.

74
00:02:24,587 --> 00:02:25,816
- We definitely do.
- Jun.

75
00:02:25,817 --> 00:02:28,426
I understand why the others are here, but you...

76
00:02:28,427 --> 00:02:30,286
- It's an unexpected combination.
- Why are you here?

77
00:02:30,287 --> 00:02:31,756
- Why are you here?
- Please explain to us.

78
00:02:31,757 --> 00:02:33,256
- Why was he invited?
- Jun looks like...

79
00:02:33,257 --> 00:02:35,326
he belongs on a herbal medicine special.

80
00:02:35,327 --> 00:02:36,667
We do have something in common.

81
00:02:37,097 --> 00:02:39,937
I let people know about these two.

82
00:02:40,737 --> 00:02:42,266
- Then you belong here.
- That's an important point.

83
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:43,407
- That's right.
- So...

84
00:02:43,767 --> 00:02:46,576
Yong Han became the best expert in the history of war...

85
00:02:46,577 --> 00:02:49,206
and Seung Byeong became the best expert in military technology...

86
00:02:49,207 --> 00:02:50,746
through their very first shows, which I hosted.

87
00:02:50,747 --> 00:02:51,747
- Oh, really?
- Really?

88
00:02:51,748 --> 00:02:53,416
- Is that right?
- That's meaningful.

89
00:02:53,417 --> 00:02:54,817
(It's all thanks to the shows that I hosted.)

90
00:02:54,917 --> 00:02:57,146
Seung Byeong, you styled your hair like Park Seo Jun.

91
00:02:57,147 --> 00:02:58,387
- Really?
- Absolutely.

92
00:02:58,687 --> 00:02:59,816
Do I look good in this hairstyle?

93
00:02:59,817 --> 00:03:02,026
- My brother is handsome, right?
- Yes, he's handsome.

94
00:03:02,027 --> 00:03:04,426
Shin Young, did you and Seung Byeong...

95
00:03:04,427 --> 00:03:06,496
plan your hairstyles together, or is it just a coincidence?

96
00:03:06,497 --> 00:03:08,526
Middle parts just run in my family.

97
00:03:08,527 --> 00:03:09,896
- Oh, I see.
- Yes.

98
00:03:09,897 --> 00:03:11,196
- We can't help it.
- Our hair naturally parts this way.

99
00:03:11,197 --> 00:03:13,136
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

100
00:03:13,137 --> 00:03:15,337
Names, Im Yong Han, Chae Seung Byeong, and Her Jun.

101
00:03:16,437 --> 00:03:17,636
Welcome!

102
00:03:17,637 --> 00:03:19,837
- Thank you.
- The three of you...

103
00:03:20,077 --> 00:03:21,906
Are these your real names?

104
00:03:21,907 --> 00:03:23,676
- Of course, it's my real name.
- Yes, it's my real name.

105
00:03:23,677 --> 00:03:26,246
Jun, what about you?

106
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:27,276
- It's your real name, right?
- It's my real name...

107
00:03:27,277 --> 00:03:29,546
- My mother gave me this name.
- It's your real name, right?

108
00:03:29,547 --> 00:03:30,616
- Yes, it's my real name.
- I see.

109
00:03:30,617 --> 00:03:34,056
I think maybe his parents chose that name...

110
00:03:34,057 --> 00:03:35,286
- with a specific intention.
- That's true.

111
00:03:35,287 --> 00:03:36,826
My mother was charismatic like a general.

112
00:03:36,827 --> 00:03:39,097
I was born with the surname "Her."

113
00:03:39,627 --> 00:03:41,496
Who's the most famous person with that surname? It's Heo Jun.

114
00:03:41,497 --> 00:03:43,496
She named me Jun, hoping I'd become greater than Heo Jun.

115
00:03:43,497 --> 00:03:44,566
- Oh, really?
- Really?

116
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:45,736
- Yes.
- That's great.

117
00:03:45,737 --> 00:03:48,436
As for "Im Yong Han" and "Chae Seung Byeong,"

118
00:03:48,437 --> 00:03:50,466
- there's no reason...
- I disagree.

119
00:03:50,467 --> 00:03:52,006
- they're not their real names.
- "Im Yong Han..."

120
00:03:52,007 --> 00:03:53,506
sounds like an alias.

121
00:03:53,507 --> 00:03:55,646
- Are you serious?
- "Im Yong Han..." Yes.

122
00:03:55,647 --> 00:03:57,306
- What makes it sound like an alias?
- It sounds like an alias?

123
00:03:57,307 --> 00:03:58,546
- Maybe his real name is Im Yong Si.
- Why?

124
00:03:58,547 --> 00:04:00,176
- What could be his real name?
- Right.

125
00:04:00,177 --> 00:04:01,416
Guess what it is based on his appearance.

126
00:04:01,417 --> 00:04:03,317
Isn't your English name Plant?

127
00:04:04,387 --> 00:04:05,556
Im Plant!

128
00:04:05,557 --> 00:04:07,516
- He's still on about the dentist.
- Like a dentist's name?

129
00:04:07,517 --> 00:04:09,856
- That's why his surname is Im?
- You're still making that joke.

130
00:04:09,857 --> 00:04:10,886
Gosh, he really should drop it.

131
00:04:10,887 --> 00:04:12,226
Where is that dental clinic?

132
00:04:12,227 --> 00:04:13,726
- It's in Gangnam.
- What's the name of it?

133
00:04:13,727 --> 00:04:15,526
- The dentist looks really kind.
- Gosh, seriously.

134
00:04:15,527 --> 00:04:18,867
I can't believe he's still milking...

135
00:04:18,997 --> 00:04:19,997
that baseless joke.

136
00:04:19,998 --> 00:04:21,066
(Yong Han likes Soo Geun-style jokes.)

137
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:25,206
Next, we'll find out about the three guests' occupations.

138
00:04:25,207 --> 00:04:26,907
First up is Jun.

139
00:04:27,377 --> 00:04:28,546
He wrote that he worked as an MC.

140
00:04:28,547 --> 00:04:30,406
- I work as an MC. I wrote it...
- Yes.

141
00:04:30,407 --> 00:04:31,476
- Many think you're a comedian.
- because you might...

142
00:04:31,477 --> 00:04:32,746
put "comedian" next to my name on the screen.

143
00:04:32,747 --> 00:04:35,046
- Really?
- Right. Young people these days...

144
00:04:35,047 --> 00:04:37,216
- think of him as a comedian.
- Isn't he a comedian?

145
00:04:37,217 --> 00:04:38,986
- Were you hired by a network?
- Let me explain.

146
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,116
- Isn't he from KBS?
- For example...

147
00:04:40,117 --> 00:04:41,686
He's not from KBS. He's not one of my juniors.

148
00:04:41,687 --> 00:04:44,057
- When I go to MBC for a shoot, - Yes?

149
00:04:44,457 --> 00:04:45,827
the comedians from MBC ask me,

150
00:04:46,057 --> 00:04:48,396
"Hey, are you from KBS or SBS?"

151
00:04:48,397 --> 00:04:49,397
Exactly.

152
00:04:49,627 --> 00:04:50,766
If I go to KBS, the comedians from KBS ask me,

153
00:04:50,767 --> 00:04:52,296
- "Hey, are you from MBC or SBS?"
- Exactly.

154
00:04:52,297 --> 00:04:53,736
The ones from SBS ask me, "Are you from KBS or MBC?"

155
00:04:53,737 --> 00:04:56,166
- I thought you were a comedian too.
- What made people think that?

156
00:04:56,167 --> 00:04:58,136
I instinctively assumed you were a comedian from KBS.

157
00:04:58,137 --> 00:04:59,476
- Me too.
- He gives off that vibe.

158
00:04:59,477 --> 00:05:01,236
- He gives off that vibe.
- Exactly.

159
00:05:01,237 --> 00:05:03,706
I've never performed in any comedy show before.

160
00:05:03,707 --> 00:05:04,776
I've never auditioned to be a comedian either.

161
00:05:04,777 --> 00:05:06,516
- Really?
- But he looks like a comedian.

162
00:05:06,517 --> 00:05:08,176
- What happened?
- Why did we all think that way?

163
00:05:08,177 --> 00:05:11,047
Back in college, when I had nothing to do with broadcasting,

164
00:05:11,817 --> 00:05:13,517
I really wanted to be a radio DJ.

165
00:05:13,987 --> 00:05:16,956
There's the streaming industry that has grown so much,

166
00:05:16,957 --> 00:05:18,957
which covers many different fields now.

167
00:05:19,397 --> 00:05:21,196
- Streamers run solo broadcasts.
- Right.

168
00:05:21,197 --> 00:05:24,726
I got into streaming back in the early 2000s.

169
00:05:24,727 --> 00:05:27,036
So, how did you transition from online streaming...

170
00:05:27,037 --> 00:05:28,966
- to making your TV debut?
- He's a great MC.

171
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:30,266
When I was doing online streaming,

172
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:32,536
- one of my viewers...
- Yes.

173
00:05:32,537 --> 00:05:33,907
was the director of a video game TV show.

174
00:05:34,837 --> 00:05:37,007
The director suggested I should audition for a TV show.

175
00:05:37,507 --> 00:05:39,376
That's how I became the MC of a video game TV show.

176
00:05:39,377 --> 00:05:40,976
- He was very lucky.
- After that...

177
00:05:40,977 --> 00:05:42,686
There was a KBS show called "The Invincible Baseball Team."

178
00:05:42,687 --> 00:05:44,747
- Yes, I know that show.
- On that show,

179
00:05:45,087 --> 00:05:47,016
Soo Geun also featured as a baseball broadcaster.

180
00:05:47,017 --> 00:05:48,986
- That's right.
- A lot of top celebrities...

181
00:05:48,987 --> 00:05:49,987
- were cast for that same role.
- Right.

182
00:05:49,988 --> 00:05:51,126
- That's right.
- Right.

183
00:05:51,127 --> 00:05:54,096
And the baseball broadcaster of the show was replaced every week.

184
00:05:54,097 --> 00:05:55,426
- That's right.
- Oh, my.

185
00:05:55,427 --> 00:05:59,367
So I called the only director at KBS that I knew.

186
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:01,937
I said, "I see that there's a baseball variety show."

187
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:05,136
"Could you give me a chance if you can't find any more people..."

188
00:06:05,137 --> 00:06:06,437
"to be the baseball broadcaster?"

189
00:06:07,237 --> 00:06:10,207
He's Director Kim Seok Yoon whom Ho Dong knows well.

190
00:06:11,147 --> 00:06:12,216
Director Kim Seok Yoon?

191
00:06:12,217 --> 00:06:14,946
He said, "Since the show is struggling even with those stars,"

192
00:06:14,947 --> 00:06:16,017
"you should join the show."

193
00:06:16,617 --> 00:06:19,086
I did my first shoot of the show like my life was on the line.

194
00:06:19,087 --> 00:06:20,456
- He did a wonderful job.
- I got cast as a fixed member.

195
00:06:20,457 --> 00:06:22,157
- That's right.
- Right after your first shoot?

196
00:06:22,427 --> 00:06:24,456
- He left a great impression.
- Jun has such a great voice.

197
00:06:24,457 --> 00:06:25,796
- Indeed.
- Yes, he has such a great voice.

198
00:06:25,797 --> 00:06:27,356
- His pronunciation is very clear.
- His diction is really good.

199
00:06:27,357 --> 00:06:28,357
- And he has a good sense of humor.
- Right.

200
00:06:28,358 --> 00:06:29,427
I have a story to tell you from back then.

201
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:31,727
"Star King" aired on SBS.

202
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:34,596
- "Infinite Challenge" aired on MBC.
- That's right.

203
00:06:34,597 --> 00:06:36,536
- KBS' weekend variety show...
- "The Invincible Baseball Team..."

204
00:06:36,537 --> 00:06:38,436
- got ratings of 2 or 3 percent.
- That's right.

205
00:06:38,437 --> 00:06:39,937
But after "The Invincible Baseball Team" started,

206
00:06:40,437 --> 00:06:41,706
our ratings went up to 5 to 7 percent.

207
00:06:41,707 --> 00:06:42,746
- The ratings kept soaring.
- And then to ten percent.

208
00:06:42,747 --> 00:06:43,776
- That's right.
- Yes.

209
00:06:43,777 --> 00:06:45,106
Each of "Infinite Challenge,"

210
00:06:45,107 --> 00:06:46,816
"The Invincible Baseball Team," and "Star King..."

211
00:06:46,817 --> 00:06:49,616
got the same ratings of 14 percent one time.

212
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:51,116
- One day, - Right.

213
00:06:51,117 --> 00:06:53,656
one of the directors I knew lost a family member,

214
00:06:53,657 --> 00:06:55,686
so I went to the funeral to help him.

215
00:06:55,687 --> 00:06:57,787
- Ho Dong was at the funeral.
- Here we go again.

216
00:06:58,527 --> 00:07:00,257
He said, "Jun, come over here."

217
00:07:01,357 --> 00:07:02,396
- "Jun."
- He called Jun.

218
00:07:02,397 --> 00:07:04,026
- The time has come.
- What did I say?

219
00:07:04,027 --> 00:07:05,536
- I've got a good feeling. Let's go.
- Is he one of Ho Dong's victims...

220
00:07:05,537 --> 00:07:06,636
even though he was not starring in "Star King?"

221
00:07:06,637 --> 00:07:08,966
- Then he said, "Come here."
- Tell us all the details.

222
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:10,107
- Don't do that.
- "Have a seat."

223
00:07:10,667 --> 00:07:12,107
- "You know 'Star King, ' right?"
- "Star King..."

224
00:07:12,377 --> 00:07:13,377
I said, "Of course, I know the show."

225
00:07:13,907 --> 00:07:14,907
He said, "Come join my show."

226
00:07:15,677 --> 00:07:16,677
Really?

227
00:07:16,678 --> 00:07:20,346
I was hosting a competing show in the same time slot as his.

228
00:07:20,347 --> 00:07:22,247
- I saw him out of all those people.
- He was your competitor.

229
00:07:22,787 --> 00:07:24,246
I asked him if he was doing well...

230
00:07:24,247 --> 00:07:25,556
and asked him to come and sit with me.

231
00:07:25,557 --> 00:07:26,586
My gosh, that's a heartwarming story.

232
00:07:26,587 --> 00:07:28,116
But I think he didn't ask if he was doing well.

233
00:07:28,117 --> 00:07:29,457
Back then,

234
00:07:29,957 --> 00:07:32,026
- if you found favor with Ho Dong, - That was the best.

235
00:07:32,027 --> 00:07:33,856
- you'd make it big in the industry.
- You were tempted by his offer.

236
00:07:33,857 --> 00:07:35,196
- You'd become a top star.
- Absolutely.

237
00:07:35,197 --> 00:07:36,966
- It was tempting.
- It meant you were a blue ocean.

238
00:07:36,967 --> 00:07:38,026
Exactly.

239
00:07:38,027 --> 00:07:39,396
I mean... Absolutely.

240
00:07:39,397 --> 00:07:40,597
- It was the best.
- Please continue.

241
00:07:40,837 --> 00:07:42,006
Since I gained so much love through my show...

242
00:07:42,007 --> 00:07:43,136
- "The Invincible Baseball Team,"
- Right.

243
00:07:43,137 --> 00:07:44,566
- I couldn't join his show...
- Right.

244
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:45,706
- that aired in the same time slot.
- That's right.

245
00:07:45,707 --> 00:07:46,776
So I said, "I'm sorry, Ho Dong."

246
00:07:46,777 --> 00:07:48,476
"I really respect you so much,"

247
00:07:48,477 --> 00:07:49,776
- "but I can't join your show."
- He must've been disappointed.

248
00:07:49,777 --> 00:07:50,777
So, what did he say?

249
00:07:50,907 --> 00:07:52,777
By that time, all the other guests had left.

250
00:07:53,047 --> 00:07:55,077
- All the other guests had left.
- Everyone else had left.

251
00:07:55,347 --> 00:07:57,947
Ho Dong was still sitting there with someone.

252
00:07:59,057 --> 00:08:00,117
He said, "So, you won't join my show?"

253
00:08:01,117 --> 00:08:03,426
- Gosh, that's so lame!
- He's the type that holds a grudge.

254
00:08:03,427 --> 00:08:04,556
- That's not cool.
- That's so lame, Ho Dong!

255
00:08:04,557 --> 00:08:05,926
- That's not cool at all.
- He was hosting another show.

256
00:08:05,927 --> 00:08:06,927
He added, "It's 'Star King.'"

257
00:08:06,927 --> 00:08:07,927
- He couldn't let it go.
- That's so lame.

258
00:08:07,928 --> 00:08:08,997
"It's a regular cast member role."

259
00:08:09,997 --> 00:08:12,566
I apologized to Ho Dong once again.

260
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:15,367
In the end, the director came to us and said,

261
00:08:15,837 --> 00:08:17,366
- "Ho Dong, you should go now."
- Right.

262
00:08:17,367 --> 00:08:19,277
- "You should go now."
- Even while leaving, Ho Dong said,

263
00:08:19,837 --> 00:08:20,837
"So, you won't join my show?"

264
00:08:21,807 --> 00:08:23,806
- He was so persistent.
- I guess I was really...

265
00:08:23,807 --> 00:08:25,746
- Ho Dong must've been drunk.
- I guess I missed...

266
00:08:25,747 --> 00:08:27,646
- Ho Dong, were you drunk?
- I guess I missed Jun.

267
00:08:27,647 --> 00:08:29,486
- He was drunk.
- He adored me so much.

268
00:08:29,487 --> 00:08:30,816
- He was drunk.
- He adored me dearly.

269
00:08:30,817 --> 00:08:32,616
- He repeated the same thing.
- I must've expressed my feelings.

270
00:08:32,617 --> 00:08:34,516
That shows how much I'd been longing to work with you.

271
00:08:34,517 --> 00:08:37,587
I must've been longing so much to work with him.

272
00:08:37,887 --> 00:08:40,597
I've hosted shows in various fields, as long as they paid me.

273
00:08:41,027 --> 00:08:42,766
I've hosted shows about health,

274
00:08:42,767 --> 00:08:44,166
- Right.
- pharmacy,

275
00:08:44,167 --> 00:08:46,296
medical science,

276
00:08:46,297 --> 00:08:48,566
weather, sports,

277
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:50,406
- video games, and movies.
- He's hosted all kinds of shows.

278
00:08:50,407 --> 00:08:52,136
- He's hosted all kinds of shows.
- I've done everything.

279
00:08:52,137 --> 00:08:57,076
Jun is known as the best MC when it comes to war history shows.

280
00:08:57,077 --> 00:08:59,176
You must have to do a lot of research in advance...

281
00:08:59,177 --> 00:09:01,876
especially for a show about history.

282
00:09:01,877 --> 00:09:03,446
Obviously, I have to do a lot of research.

283
00:09:03,447 --> 00:09:06,886
Actually, military and history shows have something in common.

284
00:09:06,887 --> 00:09:09,256
- What is it?
- So many people love those topics.

285
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:10,257
A lot of people do.

286
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:11,687
And these fans...

287
00:09:12,427 --> 00:09:14,096
get furious when the MC speaks...

288
00:09:14,097 --> 00:09:15,966
- without having basic knowledge.
- Right.

289
00:09:15,967 --> 00:09:18,167
- Right, of course. Yes.
- They'd be livid.

290
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:20,597
So I focused on learning...

291
00:09:20,997 --> 00:09:22,606
Instead of widening my knowledge about history...

292
00:09:22,607 --> 00:09:24,966
and doing intensive research like Yong Han and Seung Byeong do,

293
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:27,077
I studied jargon so that I could understand what they said.

294
00:09:28,137 --> 00:09:30,576
When I break down what they say into simpler, easier terms,

295
00:09:30,577 --> 00:09:33,276
- the viewers finally understand, - Right.

296
00:09:33,277 --> 00:09:34,316
- and that fully satisfies me.
- Exactly.

297
00:09:34,317 --> 00:09:35,317
- He explains in easy terms.
- I do that to prepare for my show.

298
00:09:35,318 --> 00:09:37,887
Why can't Yong Han use simple terms in the first place?

299
00:09:38,817 --> 00:09:40,486
- But if he does...
- He speaks Korean.

300
00:09:40,487 --> 00:09:42,186
Then why must Jun translate what he says?

301
00:09:42,187 --> 00:09:43,387
We're talking about the guests' occupations.

302
00:09:43,787 --> 00:09:47,257
- Yong Han wrote "director."
- Director?

303
00:09:47,527 --> 00:09:48,697
Did you serve in the military as an officer?

304
00:09:49,467 --> 00:09:51,727
- Thank you for your service.
- A military officer?

305
00:09:51,927 --> 00:09:54,037
- He made another joke like that.
- Yong Han must like his joke.

306
00:09:54,297 --> 00:09:56,607
- I used to teach at a university.
- I'm curious.

307
00:09:56,737 --> 00:09:59,807
But I wanted to leave that job and expand my career spectrum.

308
00:10:00,077 --> 00:10:02,006
So I quit teaching there and founded a research institute.

309
00:10:02,007 --> 00:10:04,006
- You're the director of it?
- The research institute director.

310
00:10:04,007 --> 00:10:05,076
He's the director of the institute.

311
00:10:05,077 --> 00:10:07,077
- You majored in history, right?
- Yes, I did.

312
00:10:07,817 --> 00:10:08,946
He majored in history.

313
00:10:08,947 --> 00:10:10,487
- Yes, and he's Jang Hoon's senior.
- He majored in history...

314
00:10:10,717 --> 00:10:12,657
- He went to Yonsei University?
- Really?

315
00:10:12,817 --> 00:10:16,187
- He's an Eagle too?
- I majored in theology first.

316
00:10:16,357 --> 00:10:18,527
I majored in history after getting my bachelor's degree in theology.

317
00:10:18,997 --> 00:10:20,697
So I hold two bachelor's degrees.

318
00:10:21,057 --> 00:10:22,057
That's amazing.

319
00:10:22,058 --> 00:10:24,926
So, you graduated and then enrolled in school again?

320
00:10:24,927 --> 00:10:25,966
There was the bachelor's degree transfer program...

321
00:10:25,967 --> 00:10:26,996
- back then.
- Right.

322
00:10:26,997 --> 00:10:28,367
So I started the program as a junior.

323
00:10:29,207 --> 00:10:30,336
Did you graduate...

324
00:10:30,337 --> 00:10:32,067
- from Yonsei University twice?
- That's right.

325
00:10:32,877 --> 00:10:33,906
I did both my bachelor's and master's degrees there.

326
00:10:33,907 --> 00:10:36,877
Yong Han is the number one historian in Korea...

327
00:10:37,307 --> 00:10:39,147
- when it comes to war history?
- He's the top.

328
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:41,747
- Our school only produces elites.
- Right.

329
00:10:42,747 --> 00:10:45,487
- I wondered why he brought it up.
- Hold on. That was random.

330
00:10:45,617 --> 00:10:47,487
- He was the best basketball player.
- Of course.

331
00:10:48,387 --> 00:10:52,127
Actually, Yong Han is well-known as a war buff.

332
00:10:52,197 --> 00:10:53,397
- A war buff?
- Is that true?

333
00:10:54,057 --> 00:10:55,396
I'm not a war buff.

334
00:10:55,397 --> 00:10:58,066
I've liked war history since I was a little boy.

335
00:10:58,067 --> 00:11:00,267
Actually, my main area of expertise is...

336
00:11:00,597 --> 00:11:03,137
the national policies and system of the Joseon Dynasty...

337
00:11:03,237 --> 00:11:05,237
from Jeong Do Jeon all the way to Kings Sejong and Seongjong.

338
00:11:05,737 --> 00:11:09,106
What shaped those systems of Joseon the most were...

339
00:11:09,107 --> 00:11:10,577
the wars in the 14th century.

340
00:11:11,077 --> 00:11:13,617
Since the country suffered from wars for nearly 100 years,

341
00:11:14,217 --> 00:11:15,846
they realized the need for changes...

342
00:11:15,847 --> 00:11:17,617
and decided to reshape the military system.

343
00:11:17,917 --> 00:11:20,217
Reshaping the military system called for a tax reform.

344
00:11:20,387 --> 00:11:23,427
And higher tax revenue required a boost in industrial development.

345
00:11:23,557 --> 00:11:26,457
Also, those who served in the military needed a reward.

346
00:11:26,757 --> 00:11:28,967
Improving their social treatment...

347
00:11:29,027 --> 00:11:30,597
required a shift in the class structure.

348
00:11:30,897 --> 00:11:34,067
There needed to be a reform in every system of the country.

349
00:11:34,437 --> 00:11:37,567
King Sejong created those new laws and systems...

350
00:11:37,737 --> 00:11:39,677
as a direct response to the war.

351
00:11:39,977 --> 00:11:41,607
But when people think of King Sejong,

352
00:11:42,037 --> 00:11:43,706
- they usually picture a bookworm...
- Right.

353
00:11:43,707 --> 00:11:45,747
- who does nothing but study.
- Yes.

354
00:11:45,917 --> 00:11:48,816
But in fact, King Sejong poured the most effort...

355
00:11:48,817 --> 00:11:50,047
into improving the military system.

356
00:11:50,317 --> 00:11:51,587
- Oh, I see. I didn't know that.
- I didn't know that.

357
00:11:51,817 --> 00:11:54,716
- I had no idea.
- To explain these things,

358
00:11:54,717 --> 00:11:56,486
- It's interesting.
- I needed to learn...

359
00:11:56,487 --> 00:11:57,827
about the wars and the military system.

360
00:11:58,487 --> 00:12:00,127
That's why I unintentionally ended up...

361
00:12:00,697 --> 00:12:02,567
studying the military system of that period as well.

362
00:12:03,127 --> 00:12:05,326
I even ended up writing a book about the history of war.

363
00:12:05,327 --> 00:12:08,367
Yong Han made his TV debut through my show.

364
00:12:08,737 --> 00:12:10,307
To prepare for one episode,

365
00:12:10,537 --> 00:12:13,937
he bought 20 books in foreign languages.

366
00:12:14,307 --> 00:12:16,046
It cost him more than he could afford,

367
00:12:16,047 --> 00:12:18,077
so the production team covered his book expenses.

368
00:12:18,477 --> 00:12:20,277
Yong Han, you got all those books for free.

369
00:12:21,277 --> 00:12:22,587
Yong Han is smart.

370
00:12:22,817 --> 00:12:24,746
- Yong Han is so impressive.
- Indeed.

371
00:12:24,747 --> 00:12:25,786
Really.

372
00:12:25,787 --> 00:12:27,786
I started to think he did the show just to get new books...

373
00:12:27,787 --> 00:12:29,157
since he bought so many books.

374
00:12:30,127 --> 00:12:31,227
Oh, that makes sense.

375
00:12:31,427 --> 00:12:33,557
- While teaching, you must see...
- Books are expensive.

376
00:12:33,727 --> 00:12:36,727
that people of different generations have different perspectives...

377
00:12:36,997 --> 00:12:39,536
- on war.
- That's right. Absolutely.

378
00:12:39,537 --> 00:12:40,767
They must have different perspectives.

379
00:12:40,997 --> 00:12:44,137
Since war is a horrifying thing...

380
00:12:44,337 --> 00:12:46,307
Living in peaceful times like this,

381
00:12:46,707 --> 00:12:49,307
people would think it's cowardly to betray your country...

382
00:12:49,807 --> 00:12:51,506
- to save your own skin, - Right.

383
00:12:51,507 --> 00:12:52,977
saying it's better than losing your life.

384
00:12:53,347 --> 00:12:54,476
But when reality hits,

385
00:12:54,477 --> 00:12:55,577
society becomes divided into two opposing sides.

386
00:12:55,787 --> 00:12:58,446
- To fight or not to fight.
- I see.

387
00:12:58,447 --> 00:12:59,816
This has never changed...

388
00:12:59,817 --> 00:13:01,417
- throughout human history.
- Right.

389
00:13:01,587 --> 00:13:03,326
Which side would you be on? To fight or not to fight?

390
00:13:03,327 --> 00:13:05,057
Ho Dong here always chooses to fight.

391
00:13:05,627 --> 00:13:06,926
Every single time.

392
00:13:06,927 --> 00:13:08,226
We always choose to fight no matter what.

393
00:13:08,227 --> 00:13:09,826
As for us, it's not like we choose not to fight.

394
00:13:09,827 --> 00:13:11,367
We choose not to get beaten up.

395
00:13:11,867 --> 00:13:13,896
- You choose not to die.
- We choose not to die.

396
00:13:13,897 --> 00:13:15,067
You choose not to die.

397
00:13:16,067 --> 00:13:17,567
I would also choose to fight.

398
00:13:18,537 --> 00:13:20,036
- We all have our own disposition.
- Really?

399
00:13:20,037 --> 00:13:23,877
To add to his comment, we always emphasize...

400
00:13:23,977 --> 00:13:25,147
the importance of an independent national defense capability.

401
00:13:25,777 --> 00:13:28,017
If you have the power to defend yourself,

402
00:13:28,317 --> 00:13:29,747
you can just say, "Bring it on if you dare."

403
00:13:30,047 --> 00:13:33,687
If we have enough power to defeat any enemy,

404
00:13:33,817 --> 00:13:36,456
- invasion is no longer an option.
- Of course.

405
00:13:36,457 --> 00:13:38,656
By choosing to fight, he doesn't mean...

406
00:13:38,657 --> 00:13:41,257
we should start a war to seize their territory.

407
00:13:41,557 --> 00:13:43,497
Choosing to fight is like saying, "If you invade our country,"

408
00:13:43,767 --> 00:13:45,737
"we will hit back and make sure you pay a price."

409
00:13:45,937 --> 00:13:48,066
If we have that power, other countries can't invade us.

410
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:49,807
Jun, you're a great MC.

411
00:13:51,067 --> 00:13:52,777
- I mean...
- Jun, that was impressive.

412
00:13:53,037 --> 00:13:54,636
- He explained the given topic...
- He's amazing.

413
00:13:54,637 --> 00:13:55,946
- in an easy, comprehensive way.
- That's right.

414
00:13:55,947 --> 00:13:59,347
- Since experts use unusual terms, - He's like a sports commentator.

415
00:13:59,647 --> 00:14:00,946
- I explain in a way...
- That's understandable.

416
00:14:00,947 --> 00:14:02,246
- that people can understand.
- Right.

417
00:14:02,247 --> 00:14:04,017
- You met us at our level.
- Right, exactly.

418
00:14:04,217 --> 00:14:06,686
- Jun is indispensable.
- Jun is amazing.

419
00:14:06,687 --> 00:14:09,586
Yong Han's nickname is Mr. Romance of the Three Kingdoms.

420
00:14:09,587 --> 00:14:10,756
- Mr. Romance of the Three Kingdoms?
- I see.

421
00:14:10,757 --> 00:14:12,696
- I think it was given by children.
- I think so too.

422
00:14:12,697 --> 00:14:14,026
- It wasn't children, - Mr. Romance of the Three Kingdoms?

423
00:14:14,027 --> 00:14:15,626
but this old man here who gave me that nickname.

424
00:14:15,627 --> 00:14:17,127
- Really?
- I'll explain to you.

425
00:14:17,927 --> 00:14:21,136
- You gave him the nickname, Jun?
- Yes. When we first began our show,

426
00:14:21,137 --> 00:14:22,637
he answered all of my questions.

427
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:24,367
When it comes to the history of war,

428
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:26,507
he answers any question like a vending machine.

429
00:14:26,707 --> 00:14:28,106
- That's fascinating.
- And we all like...

430
00:14:28,107 --> 00:14:29,307
- "Romance of the Three Kingdoms."
- Yes.

431
00:14:29,507 --> 00:14:31,807
As a huge fan of it, I asked him a lot of questions.

432
00:14:32,147 --> 00:14:34,176
- However, he's brutally honest.
- Why?

433
00:14:34,177 --> 00:14:36,216
He'd say, "That's not official history. It's fiction."

434
00:14:36,217 --> 00:14:37,317
- Of course.
- Oh, I see.

435
00:14:37,817 --> 00:14:39,416
I kept asking about "Romance of the Three Kingdoms..."

436
00:14:39,417 --> 00:14:41,757
since he knew the answers to all of my questions.

437
00:14:42,057 --> 00:14:44,227
I started calling him Mr. Romance of the Three Kingdoms.

438
00:14:44,757 --> 00:14:46,726
- It became like our own segment...
- Mr. Romance of the Three Kingdoms.

439
00:14:46,727 --> 00:14:49,826
that was called "Ask Anything to Mr. Romance of the Three Kingdoms."

440
00:14:49,827 --> 00:14:52,736
("Ask Anything to Mr. Romance of the Three Kingdoms")

441
00:14:52,737 --> 00:14:56,267
The novel "Romance of the Three Kingdoms..."

442
00:14:56,537 --> 00:14:57,907
is pretty different from real history, isn't it?

443
00:14:58,567 --> 00:15:02,307
- History is what really happened...
- That's right.

444
00:15:02,507 --> 00:15:05,777
whereas fiction is what we wish had happened.

445
00:15:06,777 --> 00:15:09,616
During the period where the novel is set,

446
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:12,247
the three kingdoms were engaged in intense warfare.

447
00:15:12,517 --> 00:15:15,016
So there are many characters, and the story is so dynamic.

448
00:15:15,017 --> 00:15:17,526
During that period, a civil war broke out,

449
00:15:17,527 --> 00:15:21,327
and the entire social hierarchy was turned upside down.

450
00:15:21,497 --> 00:15:23,867
Many people rose from the bottom to the upper class.

451
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:26,397
So it probably caught the interest of people back then.

452
00:15:26,697 --> 00:15:29,906
But the problem is... For example...

453
00:15:29,907 --> 00:15:32,337
Let's say Chun Hyang and Mong Ryong were real people.

454
00:15:32,607 --> 00:15:34,977
If they ended up getting divorced,

455
00:15:35,277 --> 00:15:36,476
we'd be sad.

456
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:39,946
(Laughing)

457
00:15:39,947 --> 00:15:41,117
So...

458
00:15:41,817 --> 00:15:43,747
- Only he found it funny.
- Chun Hyang and Mong Ryong...

459
00:15:44,317 --> 00:15:47,186
In reality, they might have ended up parting ways,

460
00:15:47,187 --> 00:15:48,716
but the novel would give them...

461
00:15:48,717 --> 00:15:50,226
- a happy ending.
- A beautiful ending.

462
00:15:50,227 --> 00:15:52,356
- A story can be rewritten...
- I have a question.

463
00:15:52,357 --> 00:15:53,556
- like that.
- So, it's a combination...

464
00:15:53,557 --> 00:15:55,497
- of facts and fiction.
- That's right.

465
00:15:55,697 --> 00:15:57,566
When people read "Romance of the Three Kingdoms,"

466
00:15:57,567 --> 00:16:00,466
they usually think of Cao Cao as a really bad person.

467
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:01,636
- Do they get divorced?
- Right?

468
00:16:01,637 --> 00:16:02,707
(Talking noisily)

469
00:16:02,837 --> 00:16:04,007
- Who is being so loud?
- No.

470
00:16:05,107 --> 00:16:06,237
Section Two.

471
00:16:06,307 --> 00:16:07,976
- He asked...
- Hold on a second.

472
00:16:07,977 --> 00:16:09,006
if Mong Ryong and Chun Hyang really get divorced in the story.

473
00:16:09,007 --> 00:16:10,347
- Who just made the noise?
- Do they get divorce...

474
00:16:10,807 --> 00:16:13,317
Do Mong Ryong and Chun Hyang get divorced in the story?

475
00:16:13,917 --> 00:16:16,116
- It wasn't like that.
- Who opened his mouth?

476
00:16:16,117 --> 00:16:17,146
I didn't...

477
00:16:17,147 --> 00:16:19,087
Hey, you in Section 2, Row 4.

478
00:16:19,587 --> 00:16:21,286
It was just so different...

479
00:16:21,287 --> 00:16:22,986
- from what I knew.
- Sang Min, go to the back...

480
00:16:22,987 --> 00:16:24,086
and stand facing the mirror.

481
00:16:24,087 --> 00:16:26,596
